The paper deals with the problem of detecting interesting subspace clusters in multi-attributed networks, which involves feature selection and network cluster detection. This problem is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including social network analysis (cs.SI), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), machine learning (cs.LG), statistical learning (cs.SD), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper.
